Chelsea manager, Frank Lampard, has named the Blues’ squad to face Leicester City in today’s Premier League fixture. According to Football London, Lampard has released a 25-man list to face Leicester City at the King Power Stadium. Chelsea head to the game after a 1-0 victory over Fulham in their last Premier League encounter on Saturday, while Leicester defeated Southampton 2-0. Lampard’s men are currently in the 7th position on the Premier League table with 29 points from 18 matches. Chelsea’s full squad against Leicester City: Goalkeepers: Edouard Mendy, Kepa Arrizabalaga, Willy Caballero. Defenders: Antonio Rudiger, Marcos Alonso, Andreas Christensen, Kurt Zouma, Reece James, Cesar Azpilicueta, Fikayo Tomori, Emerson Palmieri, Ben Chilwell, Thiago Silva. Midfielders: Hakim Ziyech, Jorginho, Mateo Kovacic, Mason Mount, Christian Pulisic, Billy Gilmour, Kai Havertz, Faustino Anjorin. Forwards: Timo Werner, Tammy Abraham, Olivier Giroud, Callum Hudson-Odoi. The kick-off time for Leicester vs Chelsea is 9:15 pm.